missive public, and a largely hostile press to support the women's demand. Together, they swayed the course of history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aWomenxSuffragexHistoryxNew York (State). 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aHistory : American History. 4aNew York/Regional : New York/Regional. 4aPolitics and Law : American Politics. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846631640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438466316423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438466316/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles